    With Alexa Calling, outbound calls to most numbers in the U.S., Canada and Mexico will be placed at no additional charge using your Internet service (not your home phone service).

    Excludes inbound calls from phone numbers, and calls to:

    • Emergency services numbers
    • Premium numbers

{"videoSkills":[{"Description":"Once you enable this Video Skill and link it to your Netgem device, you can use it to control your device by asking to play on-demand content, to watch TV programmes or to show the programme guide, and more. 

You don't need to say "Alexa, open netgem.tv" first, you can directly say "Alexa, Play Grand Tour", "Alexa, Watch Eastenders" or "Alexa, Go to BBC One".

To link the skill to your device, use the remote control to press MENU, go to "SETTINGS" menu (to the left), select "ALL SETTINGS" menu, then "VOICE CONTROL" and follow the instructions on TV.

Movies","VoxIconURL":null},{"Description":"Pair your Alexa device with your Humax YouView box so you can search for your favourite shows using your voice.

Once you've done that you're free to perform searches any time your box is on.

Please note at the moment you can only pair your device if you have a Humax YouView box but we￢ﾀﾙll be releasing to other devices in the future.","IconURL":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/CAPS-SSE/echo_developer/7e17/9fecadc42b1f4f898e8d46b652331217/APP_ICON?versionId=dzRxb8dYwhiBGwwtzZ78WsKLqlUqDJ08&X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&X-Amz-Date=20190709T104011Z&X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&X-Amz-Expires=7200&X-Amz-Credential=AKIAJFEYRBGIHK2BBYKA%2F20190709%2Fus-east-1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&X-Amz-Signature=b2b5a71de7f94774cc206fa2560106d2f272647320d5e3a6c181151db6f2d1c3","ProviderName":"YouView","SampleUtterances":["Alexa, search for EastEnders","Alexa, search for Octonauts","Alexa, search for shows with Prue Leith"],"SkillId":"amzn1.ask.skill.df359aff-81f2-4cde-9d93-fae660401df7","SkillInvocationName":"YouView","SkillStage":"live","Summary":"Voice control for YouView boxes","VoxIconURL":null},{"Description":"video adg uk detail","IconURL":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/CAPS-SSE/echo_developer/ada5/883f4b76fbf540159936d6116f0d0553/APP_ICON?versionId=iEjsPWUcdfSxrwcMgBGRx1qLAab0gO1x&X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&X-Amz-Date=20190709T104011Z&X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&X-Amz-Expires=7200&X-Amz-Credential=AKIAJFEYRBGIHK2BBYKA%2F20190709%2Fus-east-1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&X-Amz-Signature=6ef9fb200c8e841f003cab53e01fe977a8d6df1a5ee862ebc67d67ae0501ce4e","ProviderName":"video adg uk","SampleUtterances":["Alexa open video adg uk"],"SkillId":"amzn1.ask.skill.14fc3ba2-10f6-42b0-9207-f8fd6d17b622","SkillInvocationName":"video adg uk","SkillStage":"live","Summary":"video adg uk lil","VoxIconURL":null},{"Description":"You can now control Paper Portal devices with your voice through Amazon Alexa!

You can say things like,
Alexa, turn on Paper TV
Alexa, lower the volume on Paper TV
Alexa, change channel to 201 on Paper TV

To get started, register your devices* at https://paperportal.notfaqs.com

* only 2019 and newer models are supported","IconURL":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/CAPS-SSE/echo_developer/9e4d/9f7783b769744e0c8907797193037fec/APP_ICON?versionId=iYdEeeLvfwrQNzUjLK9TaH5k.yrUlqCD&X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&X-Amz-Date=20190709T104011Z&X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&X-Amz-Expires=7200&X-Amz-Credential=AKIAJFEYRBGIHK2BBYKA%2F20190709%2Fus-east-1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&X-Amz-Signature=9d41daaed98407e7c6c79cfb07698d1a552611bc4b86162b3ecf1fc3ebcbfd27","ProviderName":"Paper Portal","SampleUtterances":["Alexa, turn on Paper Portal","Alexa, pause","Alexa, resume"],"SkillId":"amzn1.ask.skill.284d0b2e-badf-4290-8ef2-581afa2e7542","SkillInvocationName":"Paper Portal","SkillStage":"live","Summary":"Control Paper Portal devices with your voice through Amazon Alexa","VoxIconURL":null},{"Description":"Control your smart home skill with a multi capability skill","IconURL":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/CAPS-SSE/echo_developer/426b/3da34903ee5947f2abac7cd06cdabc5b/APP_ICON?versionId=jXDKcxpJBv29h.8U.f1dZBWlIzA9ljz6&X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&X-Amz-Date=20190709T104011Z&X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&X-Amz-Expires=7200&X-Amz-Credential=AKIAJFEYRBGIHK2BBYKA%2F20190709%2Fus-east-1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&X-Amz-Signature=622bf32165a05540aef8938d230b32c6231fd3c60e38fc8e44f2976cd7042872","ProviderName":"Smart Home Control","SampleUtterances":["Alexa, turn on playroom TV","Alexa, turn off playroom TV","Alexa, change channel to 7 on playroom TV"],"SkillId":"amzn1.ask.skill.38114c59-956c-4420-8e89-0a084dc6a626","SkillInvocationName":"Smart Home Control","SkillStage":"live","Summary":"Control your smart home","VoxIconURL":null},{"Description":"With the Xbox Skill for Alexa, you can interact with your Xbox One using just your voice. Turn it on and off, launch games and apps, play and pause videos, and more, all from any Alexa-enabled device or Alexa app on iOS and Android.

To get started, sign in to the Xbox One console that you want to control, tap "Enable Skill" in the Alexa app and sign in with the Microsoft account you're using on that console. The Xbox you're signed in to will be automatically linked (you can also enable it on your console under Settings > Kinect & devices > Digital assistants). To change the device name of your Xbox or add additional consoles to control, go to the Smart Home Devices section of the Alexa app.

To learn what the Xbox skill can do, just say "Alexa, ask Xbox what can I say?" Here are some commands to get you started.

Standard commands
For access to all the commands available for the Xbox Skill on Alexa, use the standard command structure, like this:

￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, tell Xbox to turn on." (Make sure that instant on is enabled on your console.)
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, tell Xbox to turn off."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, tell Xbox to launch Forza Horizon 4" (to turn on your console, sign in and start the game).
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, tell Xbox to pause" (while a video is playing on Xbox).
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, tell Xbox to resume."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, tell Xbox to turn it up."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, tell Xbox to turn volume down 5."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, tell Xbox to record that."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, tell Xbox to start a party."

NOTE: Both "Tell Xbox" and "Ask Xbox" work for standard commands.

Smart home commands
You can also target the Xbox One console as a smart home device. Alexa smart home commands work for power, volume, and media controls. With smart home commands, you can drop the "Tell Xbox" or "Ask Xbox" portion, like in these examples:

￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, turn on [device name]."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, turn off [device name]."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, pause on [device name]."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, resume on [device name]."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, volume up on [device name]."

The default device name for Xbox consoles is "Xbox". Additional consoles have unique default names like "Xbox 4B1D". You can change the device name for smart home commands to something else "Basement Xbox" or "Den Xbox" for example. This becomes especially important if you want to use Alexa with more than one Xbox. You can change the device name for your Xbox under Smart Home Devices in the Alexa mobile app.

If you've recently used your Xbox One and there aren't any other smart home devices paired with Alexa, you can drop the device name altogether, like this:

￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, pause"
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, play"
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, resume"
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, skip forward"

TV & video skill commands
A smaller set of video skill commands are used for TV and game functions on Xbox. You can enable and manage video skills under Settings > TV & Video > Xbox in the Alexa app. Examples include:
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, launch Forza Horizon 4."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, launch Forza Horizon 4 on Xbox."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, launch Netflix."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, launch Netflix on Xbox."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, watch PBS."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, watch PBS on Xbox."
￢ﾀﾢ	"Alexa, record that."

NOTE: Your Alexa device needs to be linked with your console via the TV & video setting to enable these TV & video skill commands.

For troubleshooting, including discovering your console and working with multiple consoles or users, see our support content and forums:

￢ﾀﾢ	https://aka.ms/XboxSkillSupport
￢ﾀﾢ	https://aka.ms/XboxRedditForum","IconURL":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/CAPS-SSE/echo_developer/13dd/8463e66d65564c14ad14e3118f2f3d44/APP_ICON?versionId=pglGkX1Bfh4TMPC20bbRfwSwVgVWLG_x&X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&X-Amz-Date=20190709T104012Z&X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&X-Amz-Expires=7200&X-Amz-Credential=AKIAJFEYRBGIHK2BBYKA%2F20190709%2Fus-east-1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&X-Amz-Signature=7b4a09780585b57baec899e711cceb5a7c368f545825cba78f6171c91c34d052","ProviderName":"Xbox","SampleUtterances":["Alexa, turn on Xbox","Alexa, ask Xbox what can I say?","Alexa, tell Xbox to launch Forza Horizon 4"],"SkillId":"amzn1.ask.skill.15636948-1442-4ef4-a882-a5222c739bd7","SkillInvocationName":"xbox","SkillStage":"live","Summary":"Control your Xbox One console, using just your voice.","VoxIconURL":null}]}
